body:
- OS: Win10 version 1709 build 16299.334
- VS Code version: 1.21.1

The following tasks.json file has a weird behavior when run:

```javascript
{
    "version": "2.0.0",
    // "_runner": "terminal",

    "tasks": [
        {

            "label": "Compile Markdown",
            "type": "shell",
            "command": "markdown-it $(winpath.sh $'${file}') -o $(winpath.sh $'${file}').html",
            "problemMatcher": [],
            "group": {
                "kind": "build",
                "isDefault": true
            },

            // https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/24967#issuecomment-310993869
            "options": {
	       "shell": {
   		   "executable": "bash.exe",
                   "args": ["-i", "-c"]
               }
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

Results in the following output:

```bash
> Executing task: markdown-it $(winpath.sh $'c:\Users\lfr\OneDrive\.lxhome\repos\cnet-akeneo\.vscode\tasks.json') -o $(winpath.sh $'c:\Users\lfr\OneDrive\.lxhome\repos\cnet-akeneo\.vscode\tasks.json').html <

/bin/bash: winpath.sh: command not found
/bin/bash: winpath.sh: command not found
.bashrc loaded
```

As you can see the `.bashrc loaded` line appears after the command output. This line is echoed from my .bashrc and I would expect it to be executed before everything else. If I execute a command directly in a cmd prompt I don't have the same result:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6348118/38365583-285bdf2e-38dd-11e8-9876-0a6d9df6c60e.png)

What could possibly be causing this behavior?
